net.dnddev.factions.base

Interface Warp

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LoadWarp, MongoWarp

    public interface Warp
    A location set by Factions to be able to easily teleport to. Each Warp must have a name and location set. Additionally Warps can also have a password set in order to further restrict access within a single Faction.
    Author:
    Michael Ziluck

    • Method Detail

      • getFaction

        Faction getFaction()
        Retrieves the Faction this warp is attached to.
        Returns:
        the faction.

      • getName

        String getName()
        Retrieves the name of the warp. This is case-sensitive so it should not be used for lookup values. If look up functionality is needed, use getStub().
        Returns:
        the warp name.

      • getStub

        String getStub()
        Retrieves the lower-case name of the warp. This is the optimal way to look up a warp.
        Returns:
        the warp stub.

      • getLocation

        LazyLocation getLocation()
        Retrieves the location of the warp. It is provided in lazy form as there are times when a world is not yet loaded or should not be loaded for whatever reason.
        Returns:
        the location of the warp.

      • getPassword

        String getPassword()
        Retrieves the MD5 encrypted version of the password for this warp. A newer and less crackable encryption method is not used to ensure that too much space is not used as data security is not incredibly important with basic warps.
        Returns:
        the encrypted password.

      • hasPassword

        boolean hasPassword()
        Returns:
        true if the Warp has a password set.

      • isPassword

        boolean isPassword(String check)
        Encrypts the passed String and checks if it matches the version stored in the data.
        Parameters:
        check - the String to check.
        Returns:
        true if the passed variable is the correct password.

      • setPassword

        void setPassword(String password)
        Sets a new password for the Warp.
        Parameters:
        password - the new password for the Warp.
